





armxmn (subroutine)


Entries: armxmn
Calls  : none

Purpose: 
	Find the maximum and minimum values in a vector.  (The minimum is in the sense of -1 is smaller than 0, NOT .1 is smaller than -.2.)

Limits:
	Only for real vectors.
	Largest Max is 1E36.
	Smallest Min is -1E36.

Arguments:
	Real x(size)	data vector to analyze
	Integer size	number of elements in x
	Real xmax		Maximum value in the vector.
	Real xmin		Minimum value in the vector.

Usage:
	Pass x, use xmax, xmin as desired.
